      "content": "When people talk about the \"inner city\" look, they're usually referring to the rough-around-the-edges, no-frills style of guys from neighborhoods like Harlem, Brooklyn, or Compton. Think oversized, baggy clothing, like loose-fitting jeans, oversized shirts, and sports jerseys, often paired with gold chains and chunky sneakers. It's a look that's all about comfort and practicality, not fashion. In contrast, suburban streetwear is more about blending in with the mainstream, so it's all about clean-cut, high-end brands like Abercrombie & Fitch or Hollister, with a focus on athleisure wear and trendy accessories.",
